This paper is primarily focused on the design and implementation of D2D communication functionality for LTE networks, which falls under the category of networked systems and technologies. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper discusses the implementation of the system on a software-defined radio testbed, which involves signal processing and communication theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the security aspects of D2D communication, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses the potential for D2D communication to assist in standardization, research, and development, which could fall under cs.AR (Hardware Architecture).
